Title: The Meg Official Trailer #1 (2018) Jason Statham, Ruby Rose Megalodon Shark Movie HD
Comment:
*AVOID THIS MOVIE*

What an absolute cluster fuck of a movie. Where do I even begin with this one. A couple minutes into the movie I was cringing so hard in my seat and knew it was going to be the same throughout. But I relunctanty carried on. 

The characters and their acting were awful and showed little to no emotion throughout the film, sometimes not even mourning the death of their friends for more than a few minutes or not even panicking when in the water or on the boat when there is a huge megaladon lurking in the water? 

There was little to no suspense in the film and each scene was extremely predictable. 

Also the IQ of the characters were extremely questionable throughout and quite laughable. Like multiple people falling off boats by standing at the back edge of them and dumb helicopter pilots, who can’t keep their eyes open and end up crashing into each other? And someone bright idea to send a couple of tiny little submarines the size of a car to take out a huge shark that is the length of a ship? And what happened to the chinese destroyers that we’re meant to be on their way? Could have been a lot safer and logical? 

And talking about characters, do all blockbuster films these days need to have a character of every single different ethnicity they can think of. Do they purposely do this just to tick all the boxes so everyone is pleased in the mainstream? It’s super unrealistic and super cringe. 

I have probably missed some other dumb things but this movie was quite frankly terrible, boring, predictable and extremely cliche. Please don’t waste your time watching this movie unless you are into what myself and many others have described it to be.

Na pewno jednym z nich – i zapewne najbanalniejszym – jest to, że te wyposażone w kilka rzędów siekaczy morskie drapieżniki stanowią doskonałe ucieleśnienie z jednej strony ludzkich lęków, a z drugiej podświadomych fascynacji. Dotykają prymitywnego, uniwersalnego strachu przed nieznanym, tym czego nie widać gołym okiem, a co kryje się pod powierzchnią wody. Czymś przed czym możemy nie zdołać uciec do bezpiecznego brzegu. Title: The Meg Official Trailer #1 (2018) Jason Statham, Ruby Rose Megalodon Shark Movie HD
Comment:
Hehehe... I hate to break it to you guys, but sorry, the movie sucked. Just finished watching it, and broke into tears from laughter and the usual cinema-stupidity. Here's the review:

First half it's literally Deep Blue Sea; bringing Science into their exploration, but not skipping the usual mainstream stupidity that every scientific institute loves to incorporate; or let us say the "Hollywood directors" into their movie. 🌚
- Vacation yacht is the way to hunt a Megladon; already knowing its sheer size. A slim hook, some falling over from the boat into water, a lucky escape or misfortune here and there, you know the usual scenes... cuz, Science B**ch! 🌚

Second Half: Alright, enough with the science, we take the direction towards "Jaws" now. The usual crowded beach, cuz how else would we justify that Megladon/shark is evil, and love munching on little snacks...
- Oh wait, we MUST add a helpless dog, a fat boy who loves licking on a Popsicle more than listening to his mom, or his own life. Voila, now this completed our mainstream "shark movie" touch.

But wait, what about adding helicopters? Some gun firing(cuz a bazooka is too expensive I guess), and let's not tell our military cuz they are busy protecting our borders; we must send stupid people who can't fly, like every UFO crashing conspiracy theory. 

Hmmm... I guess this completes our movie jam packed with mumbo-jumbo! Let the audience feel stupid now. Cuz, the movie had no scope, scientific theory//approach. Just plain stupidity. 🌚

Title: The Meg Official Trailer #1 (2018) Jason Statham, Ruby Rose Megalodon Shark Movie HD
Comment:
My honest review of the Meg, I went and saw it and paid almost $20 for my ticket:

Movie overall was a 3/10 whereas Altens books are 1/10 and maybe at best a 2/10. You can tell the movie was filmed in a giant pool for most scenes. The CGI was not the best , but it was the best it could be for a B movie shark flick, however this was not a cheap B movie it was an expensive $150 million dollar flop. Deep blue sea is by far better as is the original Jaws. If they used animatronics for this movie you would probably be looking at a $500 million dollar budget. The story line was stupid but it has some very nice scenes and funny punch lines. Megalodon was 70-90 feet? Megalodon feared nothing? Hahaha Only 2 references made to the Killer whales, the creatures responsible in part for megalodon extinction. It went to the primordial sea but couldn't find tropical waters?  Save your money and wait until it comes to Netflix or some other streaming service. I wasted almost 2 hours and almost$20 dollars, hopefully other people don't have to.

Comment:
not interested in this film.

That trailer showed way too much of the shark.

That part in the beginning? Thats that for me. If I ended up going to see this film (which I'm not) I wouldn't feel an ounce of suspense.
Jaws set the standard on how to make a suspenseful shark flick.

The official theatrical trailer is also a big tease if you look at it in context (pretend you never heard of or seen the film).
you dont see one inch of that shark's face, nor do you see it visibly attacking anyone. You're left to wonder what it looks like and what else it does - you essentially have to go to the cinema to find out yourself.

The Meg, on the other hand, was already shown to me.

I know what the shark looks like, I know who the characters are and I know the shark gets killed at the end on a particular scene, because this is what movie trailers do and I have absolutely no idea why I even try to give them the benefit of the doubt every time.

Title: The Meg Official Trailer #1 (2018) Jason Statham, Ruby Rose Megalodon Shark Movie HD
Comment: This movie really missed an opportunity. You see the difference between Rainn Wilson and Jeff Bloom is that Jeff Bloom takes himself serious, and you believe it. The original Jurassic Park hit a home run with the believability of the T-Rex scenes. You actually thought this was happening in the big theaters; it was a movie making marvel. Somethings is missing with these new blockbusters. There is a lack or seriousness, with sardonic actors that pretend they are the next Joss Whedon fanboy favorite. If you go Joss Whedon, you do it all the way. A movie like this, however, deserved to be taken serious. It could have created a new type of Jurassic Park phenomenon, not to mention that there is a dedicated number of people who believe that the Megalodon still exists in the deep seas.

Title: The Meg Official Trailer #1 (2018) Jason Statham, Ruby Rose Megalodon Shark Movie HD
Comment: I have read all of the Meg books in the series by Steve Alten in which this movie is supposedly based (pretty loosely from the looks of it). And I can't even begin to express how utterly disappointed I am with this trailer. Honestly was hoping for something that followed the books (which are AMAZING btw) a bit more closely. I think a lot of fans of The Meg series were hoping for that too. Steve Alten's books have been waiting for their chance to go to the big screen for a loooong time and I feel like this movie was a squandered chance to make that happen. Instead of using the great material they had from the books, Hollywood had to go and give it their treatment. If anything, this movie will be a good Redbox rental...

Comment:
Its been decades speculating that Megalodon still lives but I find it bull.
Sure the ocean is big and have more mystery on it but I don't believe a million years old big-ass shark managed to survived till now. A lot of changes happen during all those times like the circulation of the ocean temperature and currents that affect living organisms. Quite sometimes that something weird is brought upon by witness that fares in the big blue. 
I do in fact have a hypothesis that a prehistoric shark may survived with a unique adaptation to the environment like mostly in cold deeper waters. Not big though like an 18 meters (59 ft) fish but somehow in medium-bigger size than today Great White Shark. If this kind of shark do managed to survived, I would think its mostly around the South Pacific where its the best place remain secluded and unknown to others to find out.

Comment: I read the book as a kid and can already see they missed the entire point.  It wasn't a "horror creature feature".  The protagonist was a scientist who actually wanted to preserve the shark, and the plot followed the actual shark itself as it struggled to survive out of time (and eventually found a mate in the sequel).  Anytime the shark did something horrific, it was usually because some guy screwed something up.  Also, the premise was that the protagonist was exploring the Mariana Trench with a colleague and accidentally lured the shark to the surface...not chillin' with his family in this undersea condo made of glass.

Comment:
Ok, I'll bite. The trailer definitely hooked my interest. :P

In all seriousness, what did anyone expect? It's a movie about a giant shark, of course it's going to be kind of cheesy (take those rose tinted glasses off, Jaws had its own cheesy side dish, it may have been a nice fondue but it was still cheese). I must admit I'm kind of disappointed that the movie won't just be a psychological thriller where the shark is just the plot excuse as to why they're stuck on the base at the bottom of the ocean (although I have a feeling that will take up the first third of the movie), but hey, stupid fun action movie with a kickass looking shark (kudos to the people behind the CG by the way, it looks awesome). It'll probably be a fun watch.

Just because it has a shark in it, does not mean it resembles Jaws in any way, shape, or form. Jaws had suspense and atmosphere, whereas this shows you the shark in detail in the very first trailer! There is no more mystery of how the shark will look and move. In this 2 minutes and 44 seconds long trailer, we have already seen the damn thing a bunch of times! This crap is NOT comparable to Jaws... More along the lines of Sharknado, maybe.
